    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_GLORY_LGAUSS",
    "Name": "Glory (Light Gauss)",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Glory Heavy Fire Support Vehicle (Light Gauss)</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Ferro-Fibrous</color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>3/5 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>255 Fusion</color></b>\n\nThe Glory was initially a larger version of the Goblin but evolved into a standalone fire support vehicle due to the AFFC's request for a platform for their new rotary autocannon. Despite delays, it eventually saw widespread use during the Jihad, where it served with Devlin Stone's coalition.\n\nThis variant of the Glory pairs the long-range missile launchers with a Light Gauss Rifle imported from the Free Worlds League. While two tons of ammunition keep the rifle well supplied, the high cost of importing it proves prohibitive. In addition, the lack of backup weaponry makes this variant vulnerable to enemies closing in.",
